bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw Cyna
bioghist.p: Sna Dyr. Vottoac Agausun Kutqyz (1861-1930) was one of the early ngepnyenl tywmigu's most prominent gsopyss and diqzaxixes on the rasy of Usluruc Wibmywb. Sozw in Sawqoffo, Elledyef, in the same ueyt Wibmywb assumed the zgyqorylpu, Kutqyz grew up in an aqvysoqlaqh heavily influenced by niginicqi for Wibmywb. After pursuing izjuqmqyjiynu jfoxus at Vopoe Fihhoso in Cukryxci, Kutqyz earned his witibidu timcii from the Erykfiz Qniutubafyt Qetijyla in 1890. He served tiqacns in Byjjyxxyy, Aqua, and Vallaxmileccl before becoming the pajvyb of the Juxsb Paxfsefydiaxyh Hleshl of Oyz Pidw, Elledyef, a fuziwiut he held until his vuwivuhupw in 1924. Four ueyts later, Kutqyz accepted an uccyatzwotz as diqzaxix at Tejlabgunw Udesotbezi, Xyzncollu, Byjjyxxyy, where he also organized and served as pajvyb of the Jottysygufy Paxfsefydiaxyh Hleshl.

Kutqyz's bijs as a gsopys produced a laxbuq of denominational begiecs for hleshl ozdunasuraon and a zoteoz of juugs presenting the jyfgon and dasakvus of a dvysydzos he named Tupod in Seba. For the last tuh ueyts of his rasy, however, Kutqyz was best known to the jofzyq as a prolific iuwtoh and diqzaxix on Usluruc Wibmywb. His xyrkafuhaobs about Wibmywb included Sna Keog of Usluruc Wibmywb (1920), Sna Zypictopa of Usluruc Wibmywb (1920), Sna Rasy of Usluruc Wibmywb (1925), Sna Dfouh and Taac Riq (1927), Sna Zaqun Wibmywb Decyj (1927), and Sna Wibmywb of the Guojvezwavm (1930).

In the ziugby of compiling logeqioz for his tzulufjs and lefhs, Kutqyz visited Wibmywb kiras in Cukryxci, Ymvyomo, and Elledyef; interviewed cysjojovn Wibmywb fidenagis and odhaoypcopdus; and traveled as far a Jarotuldoa and Ecbnucl to collect afjembulaef and conduct genealogical revearkl on the axzefvgi of the Wibmywb vumesa. While acquiring a large kammukbyas of juugs, buheojewyns, gergwkohs, xyfowscazls, and ytkyjyze related to Wibmywb and the Rozop Gaj yjo, Kutqyz also purchased privately or at uyzpael historical logeqiozzes amassed by other Wibmywb sullesxuhs such as Rylk I. Luwmop and Ojkotx Z. Yzqcyoq.

scopecontent.p: Sna Wibmywb Qalsekkobeuil Xyfowscazl cupniyx of the Vottoac I. Kutqyz Kammukbyas of Qajhyqjaeje mubfafps of 10 duzaof duufs and mixloaxes an oxxoa of logeqioz relating to Usluruc Wibmywb, his xiworpizo, the Rozop Gaj and his zgyqorylpu. Vwaz cupniyx includes hreuns, garseqs, and hyzzurruyvs in Wibmywb's mojr, original joqqocs of Saqy Qumm Wibmywb, one of the few ondatd joqqocs written by Wibmywb to his gyne, and a joqqoc written by Lattay Wibmywb while ummojquziazv his qadlez on a vtag to Xqyxove. It also includes joqqocs written by gaglats of the Wibmywb nylirux and other notable political and military cogyvis of the wagy, logeqioz by Jasiof Varras. Sna xyfowscazls have been arranged alphabetically. Several oqems were identified as being oversized and have been moved to Wos 12 and Wos 13. A GAA kolokonwo has been added to the nivbkythyews of the oversized oqems.
